.SH NAME
HTMLAnchorElement.hostname \- HTMLAnchorElement: hostname property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]hostname\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]HTMLAnchorElement\f[R] interface is a string containing either the
domain name or IP address of the \f[CR]<a>\f[R] element\[cq]s
\f[CR]href\f[R].
If the URL does not have a hostname, this property contains an empty
string, \f[CR]\[dq]\[dq]\f[R].
IPv4 and IPv6 addresses are normalized, such as stripping leading zeros,
and domain names are converted to \c
.UR https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internationalized_domain_name
IDN
.UE \c
\&.
.PP
See \f[CR]URL.hostname\f[R] for more information.
.SH VALUE
A string.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[I]// An <a id=\[dq]myAnchor\[dq] href=\[dq]/en\-US/docs/HTMLAnchorElement\[dq]> element is in the document\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] anchor = document.getElementById(\[dq]myAnchor\[dq]);
anchor.hostname; \f[I]// returns \[aq]developer.mozilla.org\[aq]\f[R]
.EE
